    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The majority of the marriages of our time and the way in which they are conducted make them one of the signs of the last days. Men and women are so persistent, so headstrong, that God is left out of the question. Religion is laid aside, as if it had no part to act in this solemn and important matter.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"MYP 460.1\" data-link=\"76.2363\">Messages to Young People, 460</span>.</span></a></sup>",
