    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>The Example Set by Isaac</strong>&mdash;Parents should never lose sight of their own responsibility for the future happiness of their children. Isaac&apos;s deference to his father&apos;s judgment was the result of the training that had taught him to love a life of obedience.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">11<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 175.1\" data-link=\"84.718\">Ibid., 175, 176</span>.</span></a></sup>",
